				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Kiting or Swarming<a name="48046"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 24 04 1:23 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Aside from the possible exp loss using your new charm to finish the old one, you also create looting problems. As soon as the old charm dies there is a new fight right on top of the body as the swarm engages the new charm.
<br />

<br />
For several reasons, I like to choose my charms next target and that will usually be chosen for you as the swam beats on the back of the new charm and a member extablishes aggro.
<br />

<br />
The swarm can stun your new charm allowing the mob to escape proximity. Targetting, if you use the swap target can get confusing.
<br />

<br />
Rarely it can be more convenient to have a new charm finish the old one, just depends on the circumstances.</span></td>
